---

# Recent News (2025–2026)

## AI-First Transformation

TCS leadership has announced a major AI-focused transformation strategy. The company aims to integrate AI agents into business operations at scale, making AI literacy increasingly important for future employees.

## Workforce Upskilling

TCS has expanded training initiatives in:

* Generative AI
* Cloud Computing
* Data Engineering
* Automation

The company has also announced large-scale employee upskilling programs focused on AI technologies.

## Hiring Outlook

TCS continues to recruit tens of thousands of fresh graduates annually despite broader industry hiring slowdowns. Freshers with skills in AI, cloud, data engineering, and software development are expected to remain in demand.

---

# Eligibility Criteria

## Academic Requirements

Candidates should maintain:

* Minimum 60% marks or 6.0 CGPA
* Across 10th, 12th, and Graduation

## Eligible Branches

Commonly eligible branches include:

* Computer Science Engineering
* Information Technology
* Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning
* Artificial Intelligence & Data Science
* Electronics and Communication Engineering
* Electrical Engineering
* Mechanical Engineering
* Civil Engineering
* Other recognized engineering disciplines

## Backlog Policy

* Maximum one active backlog may be permitted during assessment.
* All backlogs must be cleared before joining.

## Education Gap

* Total educational gap should generally not exceed 24 months.

---

## Package Range (Indicative)

| Role    | Package      |
| ------- | ------------ |
| Ninja   | ₹3.4–3.6 LPA |
| Digital | ₹7.0–7.3 LPA |
| Prime   | ₹9.0–9.3 LPA |

Students should verify current compensation details through official TCS recruitment communications.

---

# Preparation Tips

## 1. Build Aptitude Strength

Practice daily:

* Percentages
* Ratios and Proportions
* Time and Work
* Probability
* Logical Reasoning
* Data Interpretation

Recommended Time:
30–45 minutes daily.

---

## 2. Strengthen Coding Fundamentals

Focus on:

* Arrays
* Strings
* Functions
* Recursion
* OOP Concepts

Practice on:

* LeetCode
* GeeksforGeeks
* HackerRank

---

## 3. Take Mock NQT Tests

Benefits:

* Improve speed
* Identify weak areas
* Learn section management
* Build exam confidence

Target:
At least 5–6 full mock tests before the assessment.

---

## 4. Maintain Academic Performance

Keep CGPA above eligibility requirements.

Priority Areas:

* High-credit subjects
* Core CS subjects
* Backlog prevention

---

## 5. Prepare Project and HR Answers

Prepare concise answers for:

* Tell me about yourself.
* Explain your project.
* Why TCS?
* What are your strengths and weaknesses?
* Are you willing to relocate?

Use the structure:

Problem → Technology Used → Your Contribution → Outcome

